g statistical methods to large amount of data (machine learning knowledge a must) Deep ML knowledge and experience preferred to properly engage in the firm's Quants Complex Data (AI) Initiative for developing sophisticated components driving signals and indicators for crypto and traditional asset markets strategies/algos Strong knowledge of probability and statistics (e.g. time-series analysis, pattern recognition, ML/NLP) Experience with Rel SQL/NoSQL/graph/ databases/datasets (e.g. MongoDB, AWS, Hadoop, Q, etc) Experience with analytical packages (e.g. R, Matlab, SAS) Proficient understanding of financial markets, investments, asset pricing, macro analysis, market miscrostructure, modelling techniques; as well as derivatives, options, swaps and futures and other markets products and trading concepts required Prior experience working in a data driven research environment is a plus Independent research experience and coding portfolio crucial Ability to manage multiple tasks and thrive in a fast-paced team environment Strong work ethic, analytical thinking, intellectual rigor, curiosity and ability to grasp linkages beyond the surface Capacity to work independently and in collaboration with other team members Strong quantitative, analytical and problem-solving skills Must have a positive, collaborative team-player attitude Must have a sense of urgency and ability to work in a fast-paced environment Strong communicator who excels at rapid synthesis Benefits Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses Unlimited paid vacation time Fully covered medical insurance Remote work potential Credit toward for transportation when working late Credit for educational courses and materials relevant to work Other Work perks (including meals and fitness reimbursements) Monthly team outings and educational in-office events???????????? We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, colour, national or